.docname {Digital Twin Visualization}
.include {docs}

The **Digital Twin** view provides an interactive, real-time 3D representation of your organization's monitored buildings. From here, you can visually track occupancy, monitor temperatures, and manage the spatial configuration of your rooms.

---

## The Control Panel (View Controls)

Located within the 3D viewer, the Control Panel provides the tools you need to navigate and interact with the digital model.

You can perform the following actions directly from the control panel:
* **Reset View:** Instantly returns the camera to its default starting position and angle, centering the entire building on your screen.
* **Zoom In & Zoom Out:** Move the camera closer to or further away from the 3D model for a better look at specific areas.
* **Panorama Mode:** Toggles an auto-rotation feature that smoothly spins the camera around the building at 60fps, providing a hands-free 360-degree overview. Live sensor updates are synchronized to each animation frame so the rotation remains fluid even when telemetry is arriving.
* **Focus on Room:** When a specific room is selected, this action "explodes" or isolates the room from the rest of the building, moving the camera to focus directly on it for detailed inspection.
* **Temperature Mode:** Toggles the visual coloring of the rooms to reflect real-time temperature data instead of standard colors. Rooms will shift from cool blues to warm reds based on live climate readings.

---

## The Left Menu: Building & Floor Navigation

The Left Menu acts as your primary navigation tool for switching between different physical structures and levels.

* **Select Building:** Use the dropdown menu to choose which building you want to view. The list populates based on the domains your account has access to.
* **Floor Selection:** If a building has multiple levels, you can filter the 3D view to show only a specific floor or choose **"All Floors"** to see the entire structure.
* **Upload JSON (Data Import):** For administrators setting up a new space, this option allows you to upload a valid JSON file containing the architectural and spatial data (geometry) of a building to render it in the 3D engine.

---

## The Right Menu: Room Details & Search

The Right Menu focuses on the individual rooms within your currently selected building.

* **Search Room:** A search bar that allows you to quickly find a specific room by its name or identifier.
* **Room List:** Displays a scrollable list of all rooms currently visible in the 3D model.
* **Selection & Details:** Clicking on a room in this list (or clicking directly on the 3D model) selects it. This highlights the room in the viewer and opens up its specific details and sensor readings.

---

## Editing Capabilities

Users with elevated permissions (such as Organization Administrators or Staff) have the ability to modify the digital twin to ensure the system accurately reflects the physical space.

By selecting a room and choosing to **Edit Room**, authorized users can configure:
* **Room Name:** The display name of the room (e.g., "Physics Lab").
* **Room Identifier:** The unique system ID for the room.
* **Capacity:** The maximum safe number of people allowed in the room, which drives the dashboard occupancy statuses (Normal, Crowded, Overcrowded).
* **Max Temp (°C):** The upper temperature threshold for the room. If the live temperature exceeds this limit, the system can trigger critical alerts.
* **Theme Color:** The default visual color of the room when viewed in the standard 3D mode.

---

## Editing Building Properties

Just as you can configure individual rooms, authorized users (Organization Administrators or Staff) can also edit the properties of entire buildings. This is particularly useful for setting global defaults that apply to the whole structure.

By accessing the **Edit Building** option, you can configure:
* **Building Name:** Update the display name of the building to keep your digital twin organized.
* **Global Max Temp (°C):** Set a default upper temperature threshold for the entire building. If a specific room does not have its own custom temperature limit set, it will automatically inherit this global building threshold.

*Note: Changes made at the building level will immediately sync across the 3D model and the dashboard analytics.*